tential null pointer exceptions could arise, especially in a native image if a URLClassLoader returns null. Should I ensure proper exception handling?\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Refined `HttpMethodDirectorTest` to directly exercise the remaining legacy class helper path.\n\nUpdated:\n- `tests/src/commons-httpclient/commons-httpclient/3.0/src/test/java/commons_httpclient/commons_httpclient/HttpMethodDirectorTest.java`\n\nWhat changed:\n- Added `freshClassLoaderInitializationRunsLegacyClassHelper()`.\n- It loads `org.apache.commons.httpclient.HttpMethodDirector` through a dedicated child-first `URLClassLoader`.\n- This forces class initialization in a fresh loader, which should execute the compiler-generated `HttpMethodDirector.class$(...)` path containing the remaining `Class#forName(String)` call site.\n- Kept the previous public API integration test that exercises `HttpClient.executeMethod(...)` through a bounded local HTTP server.\n\nI did not run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_05bcafda8de1130f016a047c6bb50c819caf58fb70740cdb37\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1188, "output": 795, "cacheRead": 35840, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37823, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778678880363, "responseId": "resp_05bcafda8de1130f016a047c6127d8819c8f2a92bcf4c20bd7"}}
